question: What is SpartaHack?
answer: SpartaHack is a 36-hour programming marathon and competition held at Michigan State University on the weekend of January 20th-22nd. We provide tons of meals, snacks, nap spaces, and swag, free of cost so all you need to worry about is making something cool.

question: When will SpartaHack begin and end?
answer: SpartaHack check-in will begin at 6:00pm Eastern time on Friday, January 20, 2017. Our opening ceremony will begin that evening at 9:00pm, and our closing ceremony is scheduled to end Sunday, January 22, at 6:00pm.

question: I have a question that isn’t in this list!
answer: Reach out to us at hello@spartahack.com and we’ll get back to you.

question: Who can come to SpartaHack?
answer: Anyone who is currently a student or has graduated within 12 months of SpartaHack! Graduate students, undergrads, and high-school students from any field of study are welcome.

question: Do you have a Code of Conduct?
answer: Yes! As an MLH member event, all attendees must agree to the MLH Code of Conduct

question: What if I missed check-in?
answer: Never fear! You can check in any time at our Help Desk in A136.

question: How do I redeem my travel reimbursement?
answer:
Check out our travel policy!

Note: Only attendees who RSVPed in advance and complete all of the steps outlined in this document are eligible for travel reimbursement.

question: Where can I borrow hardware?
answer: Come see us at our Help Desk on the first floor.

question: How many students can be on a team?
answer: Teams can have up to 4 students.

question: Where can I park?
answer: You can park in Ramp 5 except for spaces on the first floor, spaces with a pay-by-plate designation, or 24-hour reserved spaces.

question: How do I sign up for SpartaHack?
answer: Unfortnately, we have run out of space in our venue so we can no longer accept new registrations. Hopefully we can hack with you next year!

question: What should I make at SpartaHack?
answer: Whatever you want to! A lot of people use hackathons as an opportunity to learn a new piece of tech, while others work with tools they know already to build something more challenging. You can check out last year’s projects here.

question: Can I work with a team at SpartaHack?
answer: Sure! Teams can have up to 4 students.

question: Do I need to know how to code to come to SpartaHack?
answer: Definitely not! No programming experience is necessary; we have workshops and mentors at the event to help you learn about a variety of topics.

question: Do you offer travel reimbursement?
answer: Yes! Check out our travel policy!
